Based on the photocopied page from the city planning technical manual, I can extract the following information:

**Figure Title:** Fig 4 Types of porches and entry ways

**Four Types of Porches/Entry Ways Illustrated:**

**A. Roofed porch**
- Shows a single-story structure with columns supporting a roof
- Features a front door and windows

**B. Roofed entry way (not vaulted)**
- Shows a two-story structure with a smaller roofed entrance projection
- Includes notation for "Height" measurement
- Shows "less than 12' above grade" dimension marking

**C. Vaulted entry way**
- Shows a two-story structure with dormer windows
- Features an arched/vaulted entrance
- Includes notation for "Height" measurement
- Shows "greater than 12' above grade" dimension marking

**D. Combination porch & vaulted entry way**
- Shows a structure combining both porch and vaulted entry elements
- Features columns and an arched entrance with tower element
- Includes notation for "Height" measurement
- Shows "greater than 12' above grade" dimension marking

**Reference Note:**
"See how to measure height of porches & entry features in Figs 6-8 on pp. 11-13"

**Technical Specifications Noted:**
- Height measurements are referenced for structures above and below 12 feet above grade
- Specific measurement methodology is referenced to additional figures on pages 11-13
